data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code directly:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your manual `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` construction **won't compile**. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
// .NET 10 — no expression trees needed
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

All that `Expression.Parameter` / `Expression.Call` / `Expression.Lambda` plumbing is eliminated.

---

### 2. Complex type column naming changes (two issues)

**a) Same-named properties across complex types** are now uniquified with a numeric suffix. Your `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` will get renamed columns, generating a migration. Pin the old names:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use full path** — `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`). Pin with `HasColumnName()` if you need to preserve the old name, or accept the generated migration to rename.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter. Add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new: redacted SQL for safe logging
    { /* logging — use logCommandText instead of command.CommandText for logs */ }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) — they all got the same new parameter.
